title: Will Hurd suspends 2024 presidential campaign
description: Former Rep. Will Hurd of Texas is suspending his presidential campaign, effectively dropping his long-shot bid for the GOP nomination in 2024.

title: Arrest warrant issued for psychiatrist who once ran Arkansas state medical board
description: An arrest warrant alleging Medicaid fraud was filed Monday for an Arkansas psychiatrist who once ran the state’s medical board, according to a court document obtained by NBC News.

title: Teens are selling products on TikTok Shop between classes
description: High schoolers are bringing in millions of views using TikTok Shop, despite the fact that TikTok forbids minors from applying to the program.

title: Powerball to reach $1.55 billion, potentially the fourth biggest lottery in U.S. history
description: The Powerball jackpot was expected to climb to $1.55 billion, potentially the fourth largest lottery payout in U.S. history, when the numbered balls drop on Monday night, game officials said.

title: Texas' Ken Paxton plans to file criminal complaints against lawmakers who impeached him
description: Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton plans to file criminal complaints against the House lawmakers who led his impeachment.

description: President Joe Biden confirmed that at least 11 American citizens have been killed in Hamas’ attack on Israel.

title: Man jumps into reflecting pool at 9/11 Memorial in New York City
description: A man was arrested in New York City on Monday for allegedly jumping into a reflecting pool at the 9/11 Memorial, police said.

title: 19 best holiday gifts for women
description: From beauty lovers to home chefs, we found the best gifts for women from brands like Summer Fridays, Dyson, Great Jones, UGG, and more.

title: White House pushes Senate to confirm a U.S. ambassador to Israel
description: WASHINGTON — The White House has been working urgently in the past 24 hours to get a Senate confirmation process in motion for President Joe Biden’s nominee to be U.S. ambassador to Israel, according to two White House officials.

title: Hamas threatens to kill a civilian hostage every time Israel hits Gaza civilians 'without warning'
description: A spokesperson for the military wing of Hamas has said militants will kill one civilian hostage any time Israel targets civilians in their homes in Gaza "without warning."

title: Students return to Vermont State University after former dean's unsolved murder near campus
description: Students returned to Vermont State University on Monday following the still-unsolved murder of a retired dean near the school last week.

title: Flag football, squash and cricket are set to be included at Los Angeles Olympics in 2028
description: The NFL’s ongoing push for worldwide exposure got another boost Monday when organizers for the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics delivered a proposal to put flag football on the program when the Summer Games return to the United States for the first time in 32 years.

title: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. ends Democratic presidential bid, launches independent campaign
description: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. announced he's running for president as an independent, ending his bid for the Democratic nomination.

title: Alabama man killed by police in 'ambush' during truck repossession, family says
description: An Alabama man was killed by police in an "ambush," his family said Monday, that unfolded when a repo man tried to take his truck with the help of officers.

title: Israeli emergency responder: 'We need to help these people'
description: Dov Maisel, vice president of operations for United Hatzalah, discusses how his organization has responded to the attacks on Israel and the aid they are providing to the IDF and civilians caught in the conflict.

title: South Asian activists call Gov. Gavin Newsom's vetoing of California caste bill 'heartbreaking'
description: After a year of mobilization and a month-long hunger strike, California’s caste discrimination bill was vetoed by Gov. Gavin Newsom.

title: New state laws will make it more difficult for schools to teach LGBTQ material in sex education
description: As lawmakers in some states limit what can be taught about sex and gender, it will be more difficult for LGBTQ students to access inclusive information.

title: NBC News team takes cover from mortar fire
description: Richard Engel and his crew take cover from incoming mortar fire in the southern Israeli town of Sderot.

title: At least nine Americans killed in Israel attacks

title: Israeli minister of energy announces water being shut off to Gaza

title: Death of Atlanta deacon electrically shocked during arrest was a homicide, autopsy says
